The paper deals with the computation of seeds in a word, which is a problem related to string algorithms and data structures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves combinatorial relations and complexity analysis, which are topics covered in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of a linear-time algorithm suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), as efficient algorithms for string processing are important in these fields.
